===Political trends and outcomes===
{{main|{{Interlanguage link|fr|2014 municipal elections in Dr<U+00F4>me|<U+00C9>lections municipales de 2014 dans la Dr<U+00F4>me}}}}

===Intercommunality and intercommunal trade unions===
Valence is the largest city of {{Interlanguage link|fr|Communaut<U+00E9> d'agglom<U+00E9>ration Valence-Romans Sud Rh<U+00F4>ne-Alpes|Communaut<U+00E9> d'agglom<U+00E9>ration Valence-Romans Sud Rh<U+00F4>ne-Alpes|Valence-Romans Sud Rh<U+00F4>ne-Alpes}}, an [[Agglomeration communities in France|agglomeration community]] with 51 communes of the region. It is responsible for several areas of skills, including local public transport, economic development, sanitation and environment, sports complexes and public libraries management.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenceagglo.fr/|title=communaut<U+00E9> d'agglom<U+00E9>ration Valence Agglo<U+2013>Sud Rh<U+00F4>ne-Alpes}}</ref>

===International relations===
