In 2011, its {{Interlanguage link|fr|Unit<U+00E9> urbaine de Valence|Unit<U+00E9> urbaine de Valence|agglomeration}} had 127,559 inhabitants (over 10 municipalities) and its {{Interlanguage link|fr|Aire urbaine de Valence|Aire urbaine de Valence|metropolitan area}} had 175,095 inhabitants (39 communes across Dr<U+00F4>me and [[Ard<U+00E8>che]]).

===Worship and humanist associations===
Valence has two Catholic parishes, which depend on the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Valence|Diocese of Valence]], [[Deanery]] of Valence: Notre-Dame-des-Peuples of Valence<ref>{{cite web|url=http://catholique-valence.cef.fr/Notre-Dame-des-Peuples-de-Valence.html|title=paroisse Notre-Dame-des-Peuples-de-Valence}}</ref> and Saint <U+00C9>milien of Valence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://catholique-valence.cef.fr/Saint-Emilien-de-Valence.html|title=Paroisse Saint-<U+00C9>milien de Valence}}</ref>

A mosque, in the city centre of Valence, welcomed the members of the [[Muslim]] faith.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mosquees.lemuslim.com/mosquee-de-valence-m5oi4108|title=Mosqu<U+00E9>e de Valence}}</ref>

The Jewish community also has a [[synagogue]] in Valence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.consistoiredefrance.fr/synagogue/1584.aci-synagogue|title=Synagogue <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref>

Protestants also have a place of worship in Valence, through the [[Reformed Church of France]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/site/eglisereformeedevalence/|title=Eglise r<U+00E9>form<U+00E9>e de France <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> as well as the [[Evangelicalism|Evangelical]] [[Protestantism|Protestant]] Church<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.epev.fr/|title=Eglise protestante <U+00E9>vang<U+00E9>lique <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> and the [[The Salvation Army|Salvation Army]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eglises.org/france/26/|title=Liste des <U+00E9>glises <U+00E9>vang<U+00E9>liques dans le d<U+00E9>partement de la Dr<U+00F4>me : Valence|work=l'annuaire <U+00E9>lectronique des <U+00C9>glises <U+00E9>vang<U+00E9>liques}}</ref>

===Cultural events and festivities===
*''Valence f<U+00EA>te le printemps'' [Valence spring festival]: Celebrating agricultural productions<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valence.fr/fr/actualite/detail/valence-fete-le-printemps.html|title=Valence f<U+00EA>te le printemps}}</ref>
*''Boulevards de chines'' [Boulevard of china]: Flea markets and antiques<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valence.fr/fr/decouvrir-valence/evenements-incontournables/boulevards-de-chines.html|title=Boulevards de chine}}</ref>
*''Festival de Valence'' [Festival of Valence]: Free concerts in the city<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valence.fr/fr/culture/festival-de-valence.html|title=Festival de Valence}}</ref>
*''Les F<U+00E9>eries d'Hiver'' [Winter extravaganza]: Show and Fireworks<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valence.fr/fr/actualite/detail/valence-lumieres-et-images-en-fete.html|title=Valence Lumi<U+00E8>res et Images en f<U+00EA>te}}</ref>

==Health==
Valence has two [[hospital]]s, a public and a private.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pagesjaunes.fr/annuaire/valence-26/hopitaux|title=H<U+00F4>pitaux <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> Many health professionals are installed on the commune, including 58 [[physician]]s,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pagesjaunes.fr/trouverlesprofessionnels/filtrer.do?idContext=395572212&portail=PJ|title=M<U+00E9>decins <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> 67 [[nurse]]s, 80 [[Physical therapy|physiotherapist]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pagesjaunes.fr/trouverlesprofessionnels/changerPage.do?numPage=1&random=0.7737979746899024&idContext=395572219&portail=PJ|title=Kin<U+00E9> <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> Since 2009, Valence is a member of the [[World Health Organization|WHO]] city health network,<ref name="sv">{{cite web|url=http://www.valence.fr/fr/sante-solidarites/la-sante-a-valence.html|title=La sant<U+00E9> <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> through its commitments for the promotion of good nutrition practices, Valence is also very active in the National Programme of Health and Nutrition (PNNS).<ref name="sv"/>

===Central Hospital of Valence===
The ''Centre Hospitalier de Valence'' [Central Hospital of Valence] (CHV) employed 2,570 people in 2013. It includes all clinical specialties (medicine, Oncology, surgery, obstetrics and gynaecology, paediatrics, psychiatry, care and rehabilitation, long stay, etc.). It has a maternity hospital where approximately 2,326 babies (including 20.9% deliveries by caesarean section and 60.6% deliveries under epidural) are born each year. The Central Hospital of Valence has a capacity of 740 beds. In 2011, nearly 67,000 people were presented as emergencies; the operating block has practised more than 10,000 interventions, nearly 29 interventions per day. In the maternity ward of the hospital, over 2,000 children were born.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ch-valence.fr/chiffres-clefs|title=Centre Hospitalier de Valence : Chiffres-clefs}}</ref> The Woman-Mother-Child Centre welcomes paediatrics, neonatology and obstetrics, infant surgery, gynaecology and the hospitalisation units for woman and child. The Medical and Tumour Pathologies Centre welcomes gastro-enterology, haematology, oncology, haemovigilance, pulmonology - infectious diseases, dermatology, alcohol addiction, and palliative care. The Geriatrics and Rehabilitation Centre brings together the geriatric mobile team, the USLD, the EHPAD, the geriatric SSR, and rehabilitation. The Surgery and Anesthesia Centre block welcomes orthopaedics, ENT, the ophthalmology, gynecological surgery, urology, neurosurgery, anesthesia, and an operating room. The Medicine and Specialties Centre includes cardiology, neurology, department of medicine, multipurpose medicine and dietetics. After the opening of the radiology building, a surgical building of 263 beds and places opened its doors in June 2011.

===Dr<U+00F4>me Ard<U+00E8>che Private Hospital===
The ''H<U+00F4>pital Priv<U+00E9> Dr<U+00F4>me Ard<U+00E8>che'' [Dr<U+00F4>me Ard<U+00E8>che Private Hospital] (HPDA) is a complex created in 2005 from the joining of the ''Clinique Pasteur'' [Pasteur clinic] (located on the neighboring commune of [[Guilherand-Granges]]) and the ''Clinique G<U+00E9>n<U+00E9>rale de Valence'' [Valence General clinic] (located in the quarter of Chaffit in Valence).<ref name="hpda">{{cite web|url=http://www.generale-de-sante.fr/hopital-prive-drome-ardeche-guilherand-granges-valence/Nous-decouvrir/Presentation|title=H<U+00F4>pital Priv<U+00E9> Dr<U+00F4>me Ard<U+00E8>che : l'union de la Clinique Pasteur et de la Clinique G<U+00E9>n<U+00E9>rale}}</ref> It has 361 beds and places spread across the two sites. Its Emergency Department, located on the site of Pasteur, is open 7 days a week and 24 hours a day.<ref name="hpda"/> In 2013, the Dr<U+00F4>me Ard<U+00E8>che Private Hospital staff consists of 150 doctors and liberal surgeons, 180 nurses, 140 caregivers, 20 midwives, 16 childcare auxiliaries, 110 other hospital workers and porters, 45 other paramedic personnel, and 80 administrative and technical personnel.<ref name="hpda"/>

===Emergency services and civil security===
The [[Fire service in France|firefighters]] of the Dr<U+00F4>me department ({{Interlanguage link|fr|Service d<U+00E9>partemental d'incendie et de secours|Service d<U+00E9>partemental d'incendie et de secours|SDIS}} 26) includes 2,735 staff (316 professional firefighters and 2,419 volunteers); its headquarters (which also houses the Board of Directors) is located at 235 ''Route de Mont<U+00E9>lier'' in Valence. Under the direction of Commander Laurent Blanchard, the firefighters of the Dr<U+00F4>me took part in 28,551 interventions in 2013. The main rescue centre (known as "CSP", commonly referred to as the ''sapeurs-pompiers de Valence'' [firefighters of Valence]) is under the responsibility of Captain Fabien Thepaut. It is the most important [[fire station|centre of intervention]] of the department and is located at 57 ''Rue de Chantecouriol'', Hugo-Provence Quarter in Valence. There are also seven assistance intervention centres (CIS) in the Valence agglomeration (CIS of Beaumont-l<U+00E8>s-Valence, Chabeuil, Etoile-sur-Rh<U+00F4>ne, Mont<U+00E9>lier, Portes-l<U+00E8>s-Valence, Saint-Marcel-l<U+00E8>s-Valence and Saint-P<U+00E9>ray).

The {{Interlanguage link|fr|Service d'aide m<U+00E9>dicale urgente|Service d'aide m<U+00E9>dicale urgente|SAMU}} 26 is an emergency medical assistance service which has the mission to receive and treat emergency calls on the territory of Dr<U+00F4>me. Its mission is to provide pre-hospital assistance to victims of accidents or sudden illnesses in critical condition.

