==Sport==
[[File:Imafinale5.jpg|thumb|right|The {{Interlanguage link|fr|Sharks de Valence}}, American football]]
*[[Basketball]]: ''Valence Bourg Basket'' is a basketball club created on 6 May 2011 and located in Bourg-l<U+00E8>s-Valence.
*[[Cycling]]: Valence was finish city of the 11th stage of the [[1996 Tour de France]], with the victory of the Colombian [[Chepe Gonz<U+00E1>lez|Jos<U+00E9> Jaime Gonz<U+00E1>lez]]. Valence will also be the finish for Stage 15 of the [[2015 Tour de France]] on 19 July.
*[[American football]]: the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Sharks de Valence}}, created in 2002, evolve in France's Division 3 Championship.
*[[Association football|Football]]: [[AS Valence|Association Sportive de Valence]] (ASV) replaced [[ASOA Valence]], which went into judicial liquidation in August 2005, wthe new team plays in the [[Championnat de France Amateur|CFA]] from the [[2011<U+2013>12 Championnat de France amateur|2011-2012 season]].
*[[Golf]]: The ''Golf Club de Valence'' covers approximately {{convert|50|ha|acre}} of woods and greenery in the commune of [[Charpey]] (east of the city); the place bears the name of ''Golf de Valence - St Didier'', and offers a course of 18 holes with a length of {{convert|5595|m|yd}}, par 71. Situated in Bourg-l<U+00E8>s-Valence, the ''Golf des Chanalets'' offers an 18-hole course, with a length of {{convert|5893|m|yd}}, par 71, and opens onto large 360<U+00B0> panoramas of the plain of Valence with the Rh<U+00F4>ne, Ard<U+00E8>che and Vercors summits.
*[[Handball]]: {{Interlanguage link|fr|Valence Handball}} played in the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Championnat de France de handball masculin de Division 2|Championnat de France de handball masculin de Division 2|Division 2 of the Championship of France}} from the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Championnat de France de handball masculin de D2 2012-2013|Championnat de France de handball masculin de D2 2012-2013|2012-2013}} season.
*[[Ice hockey]]: The {{Interlanguage link|fr|Valence Hockey sur Glace|Valence Hockey sur Glace|Lynx of Valence}} team was founded in 1976 and played in {{Interlanguage link|fr|Championnat de France de hockey sur glace D3|Championnat de France de hockey sur glace D3|Division 2}}.
*[[Judo]]: The ''CSF Judo Valence'' club was established in 1950. It now has 164 licensees including 17 black belts. Three graduate teachers of state and two volunteer teachers supervise the youngest to most senior courses.
*[[Roller in-line hockey]]: ''Valence Roller Hockey'' has a team playing in the Championship of France N2 and counts an international junior among its players.
*[[Rugby union]]: The [[Valence Sportif]], created in 1905, plays in the Championship of France, division [[F<U+00E9>d<U+00E9>rale 1|F<U+00E9>d<U+00E9>rale 2]].
*[[Squash (sport)|Squash]]: The ''Squash Club de Valence'' has a team which plays in the championnat de France national 1 with flag-carrier Gr<U+00E9>goire Marche, European champion junior and no. 79 world.
*The [[Stade Georges Pompidou|Georges Pompidou Stadium]] is the main stadium of Valence with a capacity of 14,380 places. It is also the stadium where the athletics competitions take place.
*[[Triathlon]]: ''Valence Triathlon'' has a men's team and a women's team which is in the French second division.
*[http://kendo-valence.com/ Ken Shin Kan] is a Japanese sword school which aims to promote and teach the techniques of Japanese sword are: [[naginata]], [[iaido]], {{interlanguage link|fr|Sport chanbara|Sport chanbara|chanbara}}, and [[kendo]]. The club has no less than 80 licensees of all disciplines.
*[http://valenceace.free.fr/ Valence ACE volleyball Club] offers trainings in youth and adult recreation and competition volleyball. The club has more than 130 licensees.

==Economy==
[[File:Valence banner.jpg|thumb|centre|850px|Panorama of Valence seen from the right bank of the [[Rh<U+00F4>ne]], at [[Guilherand-Granges]], in the territory of [[Ard<U+00E8>che]].]]

The focal point of major north-south European routes and door to the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Sillon Alpin}} for the east-west corridor in the direction of [[Italy]] and [[Switzerland]], the territory of the Valence agglomeration has developed around innovative companies, offering a higher education, centres of excellence and an economic supply of land.<ref name="<U+00C9>onomie-Emploi <U+00E0> Valence">{{cite web|url=http://www.valenceagglo.fr/economie-emploi/|title=<U+00C9>onomie-Emploi <U+00E0> Valence}}</ref> The development of the economy of Valence is favoured by the proximity of cities such as [[Lyon]] and [[Geneva]] and, through transport routes, major European capitals.

The economic development of Valence can also count on a wealthy producer territory of food processing, hi-tech with the presence of large groups of electronics or aerospace, many innovative SMEs and a university centre of importance of film and knowledge with the presence of major animation studios internationally recognised for the quality of their productions.<ref name="<U+00C9>onomie-Emploi <U+00E0> Valence"/>

The Valence agglomeration by its geographical and strategic position at the crossroads of the main European flows, enjoys exceptional and multimodal infrastructure: The railway marshalling yard, the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Port fluvial de commerce de la Dr<U+00F4>me|Port fluvial de commerce de la Dr<U+00F4>me|port of trade of Valence}}: River services and vessels along the Rhone by the canal from the Rh<U+00F4>ne to the Mediterranean and by access to the Freycinet northward, access to the A7 motorway and a branch towards the Is<U+00E8>re and Italy (A49) a railway siding giving access to Europe-Mediterranean traffic and Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valenceagglo.fr/panorama-economique/|title=Panorama <U+00E9>conomique de Valence}}</ref>

Valence is the seat of the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Chambre de commerce et d'industrie de la Dr<U+00F4>me|Chambre de commerce et d'industrie de la Dr<U+00F4>me|Chamber of commerce and industry of the Dr<U+00F4>me}}, which manages the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Port de l'<U+00C9>pervi<U+00E8>re}}, the {{Interlanguage link|fr|Port fluvial de commerce de la Dr<U+00F4>me|Port fluvial de commerce de la Dr<U+00F4>me|port of Valence}} and [[Valence-Chabeuil Airport]].

According to [[Institut national de la statistique et des <U+00E9>tudes <U+00E9>conomiques|INSEE]] in 2005, the percentage of the distribution of the labour force by sector of activity was:

